This looks good to me.

If you don't want to modify production code just to make testing-framework happy, we can also fix this problem with below code (only modifies test-proxy policy).

```Patch
diff --git a/sdk/core/azure-core-test/src/test_proxy_policy.cpp b/sdk/core/azure-core-test/src/test_proxy_policy.cpp
index 766742d4..5e3f3467 100644
--- a/sdk/core/azure-core-test/src/test_proxy_policy.cpp
+++ b/sdk/core/azure-core-test/src/test_proxy_policy.cpp
@@ -85,6 +85,10 @@ std::unique_ptr<RawResponse> TestProxyPolicy::Send(
     // Playback mode
     redirectRequest.SetHeader("x-recording-mode", "playback");
   }
-
+  if (request.GetMethod() == Azure::Core::Http::HttpMethod::Patch
+      && request.GetHeaders().count("Content-Length") == 0)
+  {
+    redirectRequest.SetHeader("Content-Length", "0");
+  }
   return nextHttpPolicy.Send(redirectRequest, ctx);
 }
```

